      <div class="panel-body">
        <dl class="spaced">
          <dt>Public Key Data is missing or invalid</dt>
          <dd>
            The request either did not contain the public key data or it was malformed.
            The public key must be entered in the <a href="https://man.openbsd.org/sshd#AUTHORIZED_KEYS_FILE_FORMAT">Authorized-Keys file format</a>.
            <br \><br \>
            Format:
            <br \>
            <code>
              [options] type data [comment]
            </code>
            <br \><br \>
            Example:
            <br \>
            <code>
              ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3...HUYuC3 admin@skm
            </code>
          </dd>
          <br \>
          <dt>Public Key with this fingerprint already exists</dt>
          <dd>
            Sharing keys in bad practice. Instead every account 
            and user should have its own key to allow fine-grained 
            permission of who can access what. For this reason the 
            sha256 fingerprint of a key must be unique across the 
            whole application and adding a key with the fingerprint 
            of an existing one, will result in this error.
            <br \><br \>
            The error also happens even if a key does not seem to 
            exist anymore (after deleting). The reason for this 
            it is, that public keys are tracked even after they were
            removed, preventing a readding of an expired key if 
            "key deprecation" is activated.
          </dd>
          <br \>
          <dt>Public Key Id is missing or invalid</dt>
          <dd>
            This error normally shouldn't appear. When it 
            does, it means that the id send to the server is not
            a valid uuid. It either happens when someones tempers
            with the html code or due to a bug in the software.
            <br \><br \>
            If you feel like this is a bug, feel free to create
            an issue at
            <a href="https://github.com/mettke/ssh-key-manager">github.com/mettke/ssh-key-manager</a>
          </dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
